isFinished

public boolean isFinished(NCBIBlastJobResource jobResource)
Check if a job is finished. A job is considered finish if it has a job status (not updated), and the status is either JobStatus.error, JobStatus.not_found or JobStatus.done - in which case it also need to have a NCBIBlastJobResourceBase.getNCBIBlastOutput().

Parameters:
jobResource -
Returns:
true if the job is considered finished.

updateFault

public void updateFault(NCBIBlastJobResource job)
                 throws java.rmi.RemoteException
Update faults. Currently does not do much, as faults are set on occurrence. If the NCBIBlastJobResourceBase.getNCBIBlastOutput() is not null, the current fault is removed.
